While we #stayathome our colleagues across campus are getting their equipment to where it is needed. From PPE to Energy Pods. Proud of the Lonsdale Institute, our Department of Biology, Avectas and Maynooth University Library

Maynooth University
March 30 at 1:38 PM

Proud that our President, Prof Philip Nolan, is playing such a critical role for the country at this time as the Chair of NPHET Irish Epidemiological Modelling Advisory Group. Keep up the good work, Philip! https://mu.ie/ihf16 #WeAreMU

Professor Philip Nolan, Chair of the NPHET Irish Epidemiological Modelling Advisory Group, has said it is not possible to make a prediction on the surge in Covid-19 cases at this time, as more time was needed for a more reliable picture.
rte.ie
More time needed for reliable surge projection - NPHET
Professor Philip Nolan, Chair of the NPHET Irish Epidemiological Modelling Advisory Group, has said it is not possible to make a prediction on the surge in Covid-19 cases at this time, as more time was needed for a more reliable picture.
